Here are the MSTest patterns for each scenario:

### 1. Windows-only tests — use `[SupportedOSPlatform]` or conditional skip

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[OSCondition(OperatingSystem.Windows)] // if you have a custom attribute
public void RegistryTest()
{
    if (!OperatingSystem.IsWindows())
    {
        Assert.Inconclusive("Requires Windows");
        return;
    }
    // ... registry code
}
```

Or with a **condition-based approach** (MSTest v3+):

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[DynamicData(nameof(IsWindows))] // skip via data-driven
public void RegistryTest()
{
    using var key = Registry.LocalMachine.OpenSubKey(@"SOFTWARE\...");
    Assert.IsNotNull(key);
}

public static bool IsWindows => OperatingSystem.IsWindows();
```

### 2. Skip in CI (requires local GPU)

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[TestCategory("RequiresGPU")]
public void GpuRenderTest()
{
    if (Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("CI") is not null)
    {
        Assert.Inconclusive("Skipped in CI — requires local GPU");
        return;
    }
    // ... GPU test
}
```

Then **exclude in CI** via filter:

```bash
dotnet test --filter "TestCategory!=RequiresGPU"
```

### 3. Flaky external API — use `[Retry]` (MSTest v3.8+)

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[Retry(3)] // retries up to 3 times on failure
public async Task WeatherApiFetchTest()
{
    var result = await _weatherClient.GetCurrentAsync("Seattle");
    Assert.IsNotNull(result);
    Assert.IsTrue(result.Temperature > -100);
}
```

### 4. Cleanup even on failure — use `[TestCleanup]` or `try/finally`

```csharp
[TestClass]
public class TempFileTests
{
    private string _tempFile = null!;

    [TestInitialize]
    public void Setup()
    {
        _tempFile = Path.GetTempFileName();
    }

    [TestCleanup]
    public void Cleanup()
    {
        // Runs even if the test fails or throws
        if (File.Exists(_tempFile))
            File.Delete(_tempFile);
    }

    [TestMethod]
    public void ProcessTempFileTest()
    {
        File.WriteAllText(_tempFile, "test data");
        var result = MyProcessor.Process(_tempFile);
        Assert.AreEqual("expected", result);
    }
}
```

**Key takeaways:**

| Scenario | Pattern |
|---|---|
| OS-specific | `Assert.Inconclusive()` guard or custom condition attribute |
| Skip in CI | `[TestCategory]` + `--filter` exclusion |
| Flaky/external | `[Retry(N)]` (MSTest v3.8+) |
| Guaranteed cleanup | `[TestCleanup]` (always runs, even on failure) |
